# Build the Memory Skill-Index

## Question

Layer 2+3 of the briefing answer: `joelclaw briefing --repo <cwd>` computes
heading (active arc, frontier, since-last-session delta) + a budgeted,
repo-scoped memory index (title + one-line description + page pointer per
entry, skill-shaped), served to three thin injectors: claude SessionStart
hook, pi extension (evaluate the existing skill-interpolation extension and
pi-rhizomatic as the vehicle), codex AGENTS wiring. Unfold = cached page
read (file first, qmd/Typesense lookup) with graph tendrils
(wikilinks/backlinks) shown. Prototype decides whether the literal skill
mechanism or plain prompt-index works better per runtime. Budget: small N,
interest decay hooks reserved for consumption telemetry. Receipt: fresh
sessions in two different repos wake with DIFFERENT, correctly-scoped
indexes; opening an entry unfolds the page in one tool call.

## Answer (2026-07-13)

Built `joelclaw briefing --repo <path>` in `packages/cli`. It reads schema-v1
observation pages plus repo-local and matching global Brain `.svx` pages,
recency-ranks a budgeted index, emits absolute file pointers, and keeps
sensitive bodies out of the index while marking entries `sensitive: true`.
The heading includes the newest scoped arc, frontier, and observation delta;
the day index is included when present. JSON uses the standard HATEOAS
envelope. `--format text` emits prompt-ready text. Interest decay is reserved
behind an explicit consumption-telemetry TODO. Injectors remain out of scope.

Receipts:

- `joelclaw briefing --repo ~/Code/joelhooks/joelclaw-observer`
- `joelclaw briefing --repo ~/Code/joelhooks/joelclaw-wiki`
- `bunx tsc --noEmit`
- `pnpm biome check packages/`
- compiled CLI and ran `joelclaw status`
